Code Search
===========

Code Search indexes source trees and searches them with RE2 regular
expressions. This fork keeps the current Google codebase usable and adds
practical command-line features from maintained forks.

Install
-------

	go install github.com/google/codesearch/cmd/...@latest

Commands
--------

	cindex [options] [path...]
	csearch [options] regexp
	cgrep [options] regexp [file...]
	csweb [options]

Useful additions in this fork:

* cindex -indexpath FILE, csearch -indexpath FILE, and csweb -indexpath FILE
  select an index file without changing $CSEARCHINDEX.
* cindex -exclude FILE reads file and directory exclusion patterns.
* cindex -filelist FILE reads paths to index from a file, one per line.
* cindex -logskip logs why files were skipped.
* cindex -maxfilelen, -maxlinelen, and -maxtrigrams tune text-file detection.
* csearch -all also searches regular files under indexed roots that are not
  represented in the index.
* csearch -exclude FILE excludes patterns during -all searches.
* csearch -m and -M limit total matches and matches per file.
* csearch -l -0 and cgrep -l -0 print NUL-separated file names.

Pattern Files
-------------

Pattern files used by -exclude contain one filepath pattern per line. Blank
lines and lines beginning with # are ignored. Patterns without path separators
match a file or directory base name. Patterns containing path separators match
the slash-separated path.

Background
----------

For background and an overview of the original commands, see:

	http://swtch.com/~rsc/regexp/regexp4.html

Original Code Search was written by Russ Cox.
